Safety & Information,Vehicle Information,Information procedures,Using a labor guide ,The labor guide measures time as an average between the time taken by a novice and the time taken by an experienced technician who has performed the task many times. The objective of this procedure is to show you how to understand and use a labor guide to calculate time and cost for a service procedure.,Procedure,laborguide_2.html,laborguide_pc.html,,,laborguide_WS_2.pdf,HA126_2.pdf
