Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust systems,Carbureted systems ,"Air enters through the air cleaner and passes through the carburetor to be mixed with the correct amount of fuel. Air-fuel mixture then passes through the inlet manifold, and enters the cylinders.",Theory,carbyintake_2.html,carbyintake_pc.html,carbyintake_kc.html,,,HA270_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust systems,Exhaust systems,An exhaust system must reduce engine noise and discharge exhaust gases safely away from the vehicle. An efficient exhaust system can improve engine performance.,Theory,exhaustsys_2.html,exhaustsys_pc.html,exhaustsys_kc.html,,,HA273_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust systems,Electronic fuel injection systems ,"Electronic fuel injection is controlled by an electronic control unit. It has replaced the carburetor on most modern engines. EFI engines run more smoothly, with lower fuel consumption and emissions, and more power than carbureted engines.",Theory,gasintakesys_2.html,gasintakesys_pc.html,gasintakesys_kc.html,,,HA271_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,Intake system components,"The primary components of the automotive intake system are: intake manifold, throttle body/carburetor, and air induction components such as air cleaner and ducting.",Theory,intakecomponents_2.html,,intakecomponents_kc.html,,,HA1048_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,Air cleaners ,Air cleaners filter the air before it reaches the engine. They remove abrasive particles which cause wear and damage. The filter must stop minute particles without restricting air-flow.,Theory,airclean_2.html,airclean_pc.html,airclean_kc.html,,,HA274_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,Carburetor air cleaners ,"Most air cleaners trap abrasive particles using a pleated dry paper element, but some use the dust-attracting property of oil.",Theory,carbaircleaners_2.html,carbaircleaners_pc.html,carbaircleaners_kc.html,,,HA275_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,EFI air cleaners ,"The air cleaner on a multi-point fuel injected engine uses a dry-type element. It is connected to the throttle body by a duct. For optimum performance, it needs to be supplied with cool, clean air.",Theory,efiaircleaners_2.html,efiaircleaners_pc.html,efiaircleaners_kc.html,,,HA276_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,Volumetric efficiency ,"Volumetric efficiency is a measure of the air-fuel mixture burned in the cylinder, usually expressed as a percentage.",Theory,volumetric_2.html,volumetric_pc.html,volumetric_kc.html,,,HA279_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,Forced induction,Engine performance can be improved using an air pump to force air or mixture into the cylinders. A pump driven by exhaust gases is called a turbocharger.,Theory,forcedinduction_2.html,forcedinduction_pc.html,forcedinduction_kc.html,,,HA280_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake & exhaust system components,Exhaust system components,"The primary components of the automotive exhaust system are: exhaust manifold, engine pipe, catalytic converter, exhaust brackets, muffler and components such as the resonator and tail pipe.",Theory,exhaustcomponents_2.html,,exhaustcomponents_kc.html,,,HA1049_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Intake & Exhaust,Intake system procedure,Checking & changing an air filter,"The objective of this procedure is to show you how to check, remove, and replace throttle body and plenum type engine air filters. If the filter element is not fitted correctly and does not seal properly, air will bypass the filter and enter the engine directly.",Procedure,airfilter_2.html,airfilter_pc.html,,,airfilter_WS_2.pdf,HA294_2.pdf
