Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Fuel system principles,Gasoline fuel ,"The properties of gasoline must be balanced to give satisfactory engine performance over a wide range of operating conditions including heat, altitude, and driving patterns. The more effectively liquid gasoline is changed into vapor, the more efficiently it burns in the engine.",Theory,petrolfuel_2.html,petrolfuel_pc.html,petrolfuel_kc.html,,,HA309_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Fuel system principles,Diesel fuel ,"The cetane rating of a diesel fuel defines how easily the fuel will ignite when it is injected into the cylinder. The lower a fuel's cetane rating, the longer it takes to reach ignition point.",Theory,dieselfuel_2.html,dieselfuel_pc.html,dieselfuel_kc.html,,,HA355_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Fuel system principles,Carburation ,"A light vehicle under normal conditions needs an air-fuel ratio, by mass, of about 15 to 1. By volume, that's 11000 to 1.",Theory,carburation_2.html,carburation_pc.html,carburation_kc.html,,,HA316_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Carbureted system components,Mechanical fuel pumps ,"The mechanical fuel pump has a diaphragm separating two chambers. Moving the diaphragm down draws fuel into the pumping chamber. A spring then moves the diaphragm up, forcing fuel from the pump, into the carburetor.",Theory,fuelpumpmech_2.html,fuelpumpmech_pc.html,fuelpumpmech_kc.html,,,HA323_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Carbureted system components,Electric fuel pumps ,An electric fuel pump operates with the ignition switched on. It can be controlled so that it operates only if the engine is running.,Theory,fuelpumpelec_2.html,fuelpumpelec_pc.html,fuelpumpelec_kc.html,,,HA324_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Carbureted system components,Tanks & lines ,"Most fuel tanks are in two parts joined by a weld around the flanges where the parts fit together. Baffles make the tank more rigid, prevent surging of fuel, and ensure fuel is available at the pickup tube.",Theory,tanksandlines_2.html,tanksandlines_pc.html,tanksandlines_kc.html,,,HA325_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Carbureted system components,Fuel lines ,"The fuel tank is connected to the engine by fuel lines. A return line may carry excess fuel back to the tank, to keep fuel system components cool.",Theory,fuellines_2.html,fuellines_pc.html,fuellines_kc.html,,,HA326_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Carbureted system components,Carburetor filters,Carburetor filters are used to prevent particles from entering the fuel carburetion/injection components.,Theory,carburetorfilters_2.html,carburetorfilters_pc.html,carburetorfilters_kc.html,,,HA328_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,EFI fuel supply system - principles,EFI principles,EFI systems employ injectors to spray the fuel into the intake system.  An electronic control unit processes data received from various sensors to optimize the air fuel mixture at any given moment by adjusting the amount of fuel injected.,Theory,efiprinciples_2.html,efiprinciples_pc.html,efiprinciples_kc.html,,,HA329_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,EFI fuel supply system - principles,Basic EFI principles ,"EFI is a pressurised, indirect-injection system with solenoid-operated injectors. In multi-point injection, one injector is in each intake manifold runner. Single-point injection uses one or two injectors in a carburetor-like throttle-body.",Theory,basicefiprinciples_2.html,basicefiprinciples_pc.html,basicefiprinciples_kc.html,,,HA331_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,EFI fuel supply system - components,Fuel filters ,"EFI fuel filters remove contaminants from the fuel, so that clean fuel can be supplied to the injectors.",Theory,fuelfilter_2.html,fuelfilter_pc.html,fuelfilter_kc.html,,,HA339_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,EFI fuel supply system - components,Tachometric relay ,The tachometer indicates engine RPM.,Theory,tacho_2.html,tacho_pc.html,tacho_kc.html,,,HA345_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,EFI fuel supply system - components,EFI sensors ,"EFI sensors include: wide band oxygen sensors, twin oxygen sensors, knock sensors, oil deterioration sensor, exhaust gas recirculation sensors and switches.",Theory,eficompsensors_2.html,,,,,HA347_2.pdf
Fuel Systems,Fuels & Fuel Supply,Fuel system procedures,Replacing a fuel filter,There are two types of fuel filter: carbureted system filter and EFI system filter. It is important to follow the correct procedure for the type of vehicle you are servicing. The objective of this procedure is to show you how to remove and replace a fuel filter.,Procedure,repfuelfilter_2.html,repfuelfilter_pc.html,,,repfuelfilter_WS_2.pdf,HA352_2.pdf
