Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Tire types & characteristics ,Tires ,"Tires are mainly made from synthetic materials. They can be tubed or tubeless, with different types of construction, profile and speed ratings.",Theory,tires_2.html,tires_pc.html,tires_kc.html,,,HA487_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Tire types & characteristics ,Radial ply tires ,"Radial ply tires use two or more layers of casing plies, with the cord loops running radially from bead to bead.",Theory,radialplytires_2.html,radialplytires_pc.html,radialplytires_kc.html,,,HA488_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Tire types & characteristics ,Radial ply tire sidewalls ,"A tire-wheel assembly must be balanced. As the wheel rotates, centrifugal force acts outwards. Any heavier part will vibrate vertically, and slap the road surface with each wheel revolution.",Theory,sidewall_2.html,sidewall_pc.html,sidewall_kc.html,,,HA489_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Tire construction,Tire materials ,Manufacturers use a sophisticated selection process to create combinations that provide the required performance characteristics and 'hysteresis level' of the tire. Having fewer plies makes a tire more flexible. Higher numbers of plies make its response to bumps harsher.,Theory,tiremat_2.html,tiremat_pc.html,tiremat_kc.html,,,HA496_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Tire construction,Tire sizes & designations ,"Aspect ratio is the ratio of a tire's height to its width. The lower the aspect ratio, the wider the tire is in relation to its height.",Theory,tiresize_2.html,tiresize_pc.html,tiresize_kc.html,,,HA498_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Tire construction,Tire information ,"Aspect ratio is included in the sidewall marking, with the type of construction, and the speed rating. Metric-diameter rims cannot be fitted with imperial-diameter tires, or vice-versa.",Theory,tireinfo_2.html,tireinfo_pc.html,tireinfo_kc.html,,,HA499_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Basic principles of wheel alignment ,"If wheels are properly aligned, the steering wheel will tend to stay in a straight-ahead position on straight, level roads. Similarly, little effort should be needed to turn the vehicle into curves.",Theory,wheelalignment_2.html,wheelalignment_pc.html,wheelalignment_kc.html,,,HA502_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Caster ,"Caster is the angle between the steering axis centerline, and a vertical line through the center of the wheel. Backward tilt from the vertical line is positive caster. Forward tilt is negative caster.",Theory,caster_2.html,caster_pc.html,caster_kc.html,,,HA503_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Camber ,"Viewed from vehicle front, camber is the angle of tilt of the wheel from the vertical. A wheel leaning away from the vehicle at the top has positive camber. Leaning towards the vehicle, it has negative camber.",Theory,camber_2.html,camber_pc.html,camber_kc.html,,,HA504_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Scrub radius ,"The effect of scrub radius is to provide a turning moment which attempts to turn the wheel away from the central position, when the vehicle is in motion.",Theory,scrubradius_2.html,scrubradius_pc.html,scrubradius_kc.html,,,HA505_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Steering axis inclination ,"As the wheel assembly swivels, it turns around the steering axis, on a line drawn through the upper and lower pivot points of the suspension assembly. Seen from the front of the car, it tilts inward.",Theory,steeringaxis_2.html,steeringaxis_pc.html,steeringaxis_kc.html,,,HA506_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Toe-in & toe out ,"Toe angles ensure that wheels are in line with the direction of travel. In the straight-ahead position, the wheels may have toe-in or toe-out, depending on manufacturer's specifications.",Theory,toeinandout_2.html,toeinandout_pc.html,toeinandout_kc.html,,,HA507_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Toe-out on turns ,Toe-out on turns is the relative toe setting of the front wheels as they turn to the left or right.,Theory,toeoutturns_2.html,toeoutturns_pc.html,toeoutturns_kc.html,,,HA508_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheel alignment fundamentals,Turning radius ,The turning radius is a measure of the vehicles turning circle when the steering wheel is turned to its limit.,Theory,turningradius_2.html,turningradius_pc.html,turningradius_kc.html,,,HA509_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheels & tires procedures,Using a tire pressure gauge ,There are two main types of tire pressure gauges: fixed workshop gauges and portable pocket size gauges. The objective of this procedure is to show you how to use a tire pressure gauge and interpret the readings correctly.,Procedure,tirepressgauge_2.html,tirepressgauge_pc.html,,,tirepressgauge_WS_2.pdf,HA511_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheels & tires procedures,Checking & adjusting tire pressure ,The tire pressures should be checked when the tires are cold. The objective of this procedure is to show you how to check and adjust tire pressures to correct levels. Check the owner's manual or the tire decal usually located on the driver's side door jam for correct pressures.,Procedure,adjpress_2.html,adjpress_pc.html,,,adjpress_WS_2.pdf,HA512_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheels & tires procedures,Checking for tire wear patterns ,The objective of this procedure is to show you how to check tire for correct wear pattern and ensure there are no embedded foreign objects in the tread. Remember to check the spare or emergency rim as well as the four fitted tires.,Procedure,tirewear_2.html,tirewear_pc.html,,,tirewear_WS_2.pdf,HA513_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheels & tires procedures,Rotating tires ,The objective of this procedure is to show you how to rotate tires to meet the manufacturer's requirements. Some tires are directional; they are designed to turn in one direction only. The majority of tires can be mounted and run in either direction.,Procedure,rotatetires_2.html,rotatetires_pc.html,,,rotatetires_WS_2.pdf,HA514_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheels & tires procedures,Removing a tire ,An inflated tire is a pressure vessel that must be treated with care and respect. Always fully deflate the tire before performing any repair tasks. The objective of this procedure is to show you how to safely remove a vehicle tire from a rim.,Procedure,removetire_2.html,removetire_pc.html,,,removetire_WS_2.pdf,HA515_2.pdf
Steering & Suspension,Wheels & Tires,Wheels & tires procedures,Fitting a tire ,The objective of this procedure is to show you how to safely fit a vehicle tire to a rim. Always check with specifications on the tire machine you are using before proceeding with the mounting of the tire to avoid damage to the rim.,Procedure,fittingtire_2.html,fittingtire_pc.html,,,fittingtire_WS_2.pdf,HA516_2.pdf
